# Copy the target you use to a gitignored local file, then fill in secrets.
#
# Remote Supabase (default for this project):
#   cp .env.remote.example .env.remote.local
#
# Local Postgres on your machine:
#   cp .env.local.example .env.local.local
#
# Normal real-API development uses `pnpm dev:stack:local`; these copies remain
# supported as manual Wrangler fallbacks.
#
# Wrangler loads .env, .env.local, .env.<env>, and .env.<env>.local when you pass
# --env local or --env remote (see package.json dev:* scripts).
